question: Following are spectroscopic and analytical characteristics for an unknown compound. Propose a structure. Empirical formula: $\ce{C_8H_{16}O}$. $^1H$ NMR: $\delta$ =  0.90 (t, 3 H), 1.0–1.6 (m, 8 H), 2.05 (s, 3 H), and 2.25 (t, 2 H) ppm. IR : 1715 $cm^{-1}$. UV: $\lambda_{max}(\epsilon) = 280(15) \ nm$. MS: $m/z$ = 128 ($M^{+·}$);  intensity of $(M + 1)^+$ peak is 9% of $M^{+·}$ peak; important fragments are at $m/z=113(M - 15)^+$ ,$m/z=85(M - 43)^+$ ,$m/z=71(M - 57)^+$,$m/z=58(M - 70)^+$ (the second largest peak), and $m/z=43(M - 85)^+$ (the base peak).
